						<summary>

						<p>c. 10th-11th Century.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is in verse and praises Chōḻa-chēndaṉ-kōṉ of Iḍattuvaḷi as the lord of Kumbaṉūr, Kuraṇḍi, Kuṉṟattūr, and Puttūr. He is said to be a scion of the family of Chāttaṉ.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">Virudhunagar District Inscriptions</hi>, No. 143/2005]</p>						

						</summary>
